==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tonguing
<hw>Tongu"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>vb. n.</pos> <fld>(Music)</fld>
<def>Modification of tone for a rapid staccato effect by the performer's
tongue, in playing a wind instrument, as a flute. In <stype>single
tonguing</stype> only one kind of stroke is used, the tongue
articulating a rapid ⟦ldquo⟧t;⟦rdquo⟧ in <stype>double tonguing</stype>,
two strokes, as for ⟦ldquo⟧t⟦rdquo⟧ and ⟦ldquo⟧k,⟦rdquo⟧ are alternated;
in <stype>triple tonguing</stype>, ⟦ldquo⟧t, k, t,⟦rdquo⟧ etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tonguy</ent>⟦br⟧
